  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Previous studies have shown that peripheral muscles weakness or inhibition is related to
      spinal disorders. Passive mobilization and manipulation are likely to reverse such muscle
      weakness. The purpose of the study was to assess the effect of spinal mobilization on the
      maximal muscle strength of the hip flexors and motor function.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
